-- Villanova Upsets Louisville; Kansas Remains Unbeaten in Big 12
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-01-23T05:11:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-23/villanova-upsets-louisville-kansas-remains-unbeaten-in-big-12.html
Villanova University toppled the
fifth-ranked University of Louisville 73-64 while No. 3  Kansas 
defeated 11th-ranked Kansas State 59-55 in college basketball.  Ryan Arcidiacono scored 15 points and Mouphtaou Yarou,
Darrun Hilliard and JayVaughn Pinkston each contributed 11
points last night for the Wildcats at the Pavilion in Villanova,
 Pennsylvania .  Villanova (12-7, 3-3  Big East ) had a 30-28 halftime lead
and outscored the Cardinals 43-36 in the second half.  Wayne Blackshear had a game-high 17 points for Louisville
(16-3, 4-2 Big East), which has lost two straight games, and
Peyton Siva scored 15 points.  At Fred Bramlage Coliseum in Manhattan, Kansas, Travis
Releford scored 12 points to help the Jayhawks (17-1) remain
undefeated through five Big 12 Conference games. Ben McLemore
added 11 points and Jeff Withey had 11 points and 10 rebounds
for Kansas.  Shane Southwell scored 19 points, Rodney McGruder added 13
and Angel Rodriguez had 12 points for Kansas State (15-3), which
fell to 4-1 in the Big 12.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
